      "instruction": "<p>Add the contents of your pan<strong> </strong>to the<strong> slow cooker</strong></p><p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and<strong> tomato paste </strong>with your<strong> balsamic vinegar, dried basil </strong>and<strong> chopped potatoes</strong></p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong>, then cover and cook on high for 4 hours (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Greek-style lamb stew</strong></p>",
